Response ID: resp_3966
Response Text: You should make sure artist know about them. I've been an artist here for over 50 years and only heard about a couple of them. I just looked at the eligibility for the Creative Space grant and one has to already have a commercial space. Well many artists simply cannot afford a commercial space--which is why they need assistance in the first place. A painter friend of mine has not been able to afford a studio for over a decade due to high rents in Austin--she can scarcely afford a home. In fact she has to share a home to keep a roof over her head and all her art supplies and paintings are in storage. Austin is missing their artists in part for this reason. The other part is lots of money is going to nefarious non-profit groups that are not transparent and are taking advantage of this system of grants. Let's fund some of the little people!!

